default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultPublic Highways and Rights of Way:  defaultOur members are not to any great extent affected, positively or negatively by the current proposals in sections 12-18 of the Bill and the associated Schedules. However, we support the work and recommendations of the Stakeholder Working Group (SWG) on which we were represented LARA. 
default•
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe proposals from the SWG were arrived at by a consensus approach. In fact it was an agreement within the SWG that only proposals agreed by all parties would be put forward and that they were intended to be a package of measures and not to be cherry picked.
default•
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe welcome this consensus approach and believe there is more to be achieved by continuing the work of the SWG.
default•
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe note that certain members of the SWG are submitting evidence that breaks ranks with 
defaultthe  SWG
default principles of consensus which we deplore and 
defaultare at best disingenuous. 
default•
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe SWG was set up to find alternatives to the Discovering Lost Ways Project. We think the current proposals are a step in the right direction and as such are supported but there is more to do. Implementing the existing proposals as set out in the Bill will confirm the consensus approach and enable to SWG to continue its work.
default•
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultGLASS have been active in assisting local authorities recording public rights and are aware of the excessive burden for the Definitive Map Modification Order (DMMO) process introduced in the 1981 Wildlife &amp; Countryside Act 
defaultand believe the SWG has the ability to seek further deregulation of this process. 
default•
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe are also concerned that some groups/organisations are promoting a proposal that that all unsealed public roads and byways open to all traffic are administratively downgraded to restricted byway status.
default•
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe believe that there is no evidential case made for any of these proposals, and that they will introduce an additional layer of regulation and burden, and that any change in this area of law and practice should first go through a proper process of public consultation.
default•
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultCountryside access organisation is an emotive topic and impacts on Land Owners, Local Authorities, and Rights of Way (ROW) user organisations.  Scotland has 
defaulteffectivly
default deregulated it ROW structure and Wales is consulting on similar proposals at this time.  Any restriction to access that is considered should be properly consulted on and examined by the governments own advisers in this area before making recommendations for change.
